user_message:
An agent A claimed that the following list_directory code violates the MISRA C 2023 rule 8.13.
<misra_rule>
MISRA C 2023 Rule 8.13 is A pointer should point to a const-qualified type whenever possible.

</misra_rule>
<target_code>
Here is the original code of list_directory.
```c
static enum MHD_Result
list_directory (struct ResponseDataContext *rdc,
                const char *dirname)
{
  char fullname[PATH_MAX];
  struct stat sbuf;
  DIR *dir;
  struct dirent *de;

  if (NULL == (dir = opendir (dirname)))
    return MHD_NO;
  while (NULL != (de = readdir (dir)))
  {
    int res;
    if ('.' == de->d_name[0])
      continue;
    if (sizeof (fullname) <= (unsigned int)
        snprintf (fullname, sizeof (fullname),
                  "%s/%s",
                  dirname, de->d_name))
      continue;  /* ugh, file too long? how can this be!? */
    if (0 != stat (fullname, &sbuf))
      continue;  /* ugh, failed to 'stat' */
    if (! S_ISREG (sbuf.st_mode))
      continue;  /* not a regular file, skip */
    if (rdc->off + 1024 > rdc->buf_len)
    {
      void *r;

      if ( (2 * rdc->buf_len + 1024) < rdc->buf_len)
        break; /* more than SIZE_T _index_ size? Too big for us */
      rdc->buf_len = 2 * rdc->buf_len + 1024;
      if (NULL == (r = realloc (rdc->buf, rdc->buf_len)))
        break; /* out of memory */
      rdc->buf = r;
    }
    res = snprintf (&rdc->buf[rdc->off],
                    rdc->buf_len - rdc->off,
                    "<li><a href=\"/%s\">%s</a></li>\n",
                    fullname,
                    de->d_name);
    if (0 >= res)
      continue;  /* snprintf() error */
    if (rdc->buf_len - rdc->off <= (size_t) res)
      continue;  /* buffer too small?? */
    rdc->off += (size_t) res;
  }
  (void) closedir (dir);
  return MHD_YES;
}
```
</target_code>
<response format>
Provide your answer with these fields.
- explanation: your evaluation of the scenario provided by the agent A.
- is_report_correct: whether the report is correct or not (true/false). True means there is a violation.
</response format>
<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The pointer 'de' is declared as 'struct dirent *de;' but in the function it is only read (de->d_name is used) and never modified. According to MISRA C 2023 Rule 8.13 it should be const-qualified when possible. Changing the declaration to 'const struct dirent *de;' (assigning the result of readdir() to a pointer-to-const is permitted) prevents accidental modification and satisfies the rule.
</scenario>
